  <text>
    <body>
      <div subtype="original" type="letter" xml:id="L.8087" xml:lang="en">
        <pb facs="#IMG.1" n="1"/>
        <dateline>Panjab Notes and Queries<lb/> EDITOR’S OFFICE<lb/> AMBÁLÁ, PANJÁB, INDIA <hi rend="unknown" rendition="#none">Dated</hi> 19-9-1884 </dateline>
        <opener>Dear Sir,</opener>
        <p>Thus after 25<hi rendition="#sup">th</hi> Aug. I am really at Simla in the hills<note n="1" place="foot" type="editorial">Shimla (früher Simla) ist die Hauptstadt des nordindischen Bundesstaats Himachal Pradesh, der in den Ausläufern des Himalaya-Gebirges liegt.</note> for a month trying to recover from an attack of optic neuralgia brought on by overwork, which as you may imagine, is a chronic complaint with me!</p>

        <p>You are quite welcome to keep my M.S.S. &amp;amp; use them at your leisure &amp;amp; pray do not work at them too soon after your illness in order to send them back to me <pb
            facs="#IMG.2" n="2"/> soon. I am in no hurry to get them back again. I am glad to think you will find them of use.</p>
        <p>You will see that we make cites of corrupt English etc in my paper from time to time &amp;amp; I hope you will find them useful.</p>
        <p>I see the 1<hi rendition="#sup">st</hi> volume of my Legends of the Panjab<note n="2" place="foot" type="editorial">
            <bibl>
              <ref target="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.bibliography#BIBL.7576">Captain Richard Carnac Temple, <hi
                  rend="unknown" rendition="#none">The Legens of the Panjâb</hi>. Vol., 1, Bombay: Education Society's Press London: Trübner, [1884].</ref>
            </bibl>

          </note> is highly spoken of in England &amp;amp; France which is gratifying but I wish it sold better, at present I am a much heavier loser over the sale than I can afford. I have <pb
            facs="#IMG.3"
            n="3"/> commenced vol II but unless the sale increases a good deal I shall have to stop the other volumes which will be a disappointment as the material is <hi
            rend="unknown" rendition="#none">all new</hi>.</p>
        <p>I am editing the late D<hi
            rendition="#sup">r</hi> Fallon‘s Hindustani Proverbs (12,500) for his executers. One part is out.<note n="3"
            place="foot" type="editorial">Samuel W. Fallon, <bibl>
              <ref target="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.bibliography#BIBL.4844">
                <hi rend="unknown" rendition="#none">Hindustani-English Dictionary of idioms and proverbs</hi>
              </ref>
            </bibl>, Banares: Medical Hall Press, 1886.</note>
        </p>
        <p>The Notes &amp;amp; Queries is getting on very well indeed, I am glad to say, I am doubling the size of it next month.</p>
        <p>The notices are out that M<hi rendition="#sup">r</hi> Fleet,<note n="4" place="foot" type="editorial">

            <persName>
John Faithful Fleet</persName> (1847-1917), Historiker, Epigraphiker u. Linguist, engl. Beamter im indischen öffentlichen Dienst.</note> the Epigraphist, &amp;amp; myself are to edit the Indian Antiquary from next January.<note
            n="5" place="foot" type="editorial">
            <hi rend="unknown"
            rendition="#none">
The Indian Antiquary</hi>. A journal of oriental research in archaeology, history, literature, language, philosophy, religion, folklore, &amp;amp;c, &amp;amp;c, ersch. Zw. 1872 u. 1933. Der erste Hrsg. <persName>

James Burgess</persName> mußte wegen ernster Augenprobleme sein Amt aufgeben.</note> I hope it will be as successful in the hands as in those of D<hi rendition="#sup">r</hi> Burgess</p>
        <closer>
          <salute>Yours truly</salute>
          <signed>
            <persName ref="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.persons#P.2844">RTemple</persName>
          </signed>
        </closer>
      </div>
